    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan I've designed after thoroughly exploring the codebase:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `ollama rename` to Ollama\n\n**4 files to touch**, all following the existing `copy`/`delete` patterns exactly.\n\n### 1. `api/types.go` — New `RenameRequest` struct\nInsert right after `CopyRequest` (line 765). Identical shape: `Source` + `Destination` string fields.\n\n### 2. `api/client.go` — New `Rename()` client method\nInsert after `Copy()` (line 387). POSTs to `/api/rename`, no response body — a direct clone of `Copy()`.\n\n### 3. `server/routes.go` — New `RenameHandler` + route registration\n\nThe handler (inserted after `CopyHandler` at line 1483) follows this sequence:\n1. Bind & validate JSON request body\n2. Parse + validate both `src` and `dst` model names (`model.ParseName` → `getExistingName`)\n3. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → **404** if `os.IsNotExist`\n4. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` → **409** if it *succeeds* (destination already exists)\n5. `CopyModel(src, dst)` — copies only the manifest file; blobs are shared by digest reference\n6. `srcManifest.Remove()` — deletes the source manifest file + prunes empty dirs\n7. `srcManifest.RemoveLayers()` — scans all remaining manifests and deletes only truly orphaned blobs (safe: `dst` now holds all the same digest references)\n8. HTTP 200, empty body on success\n\nRoute registration: `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` after line 1698.\n\n### 4. `cmd/cmd.go` — New `RenameHandler` CLI func + `renameCmd` cobra command\n\n- `RenameHandler` (after `CopyHandler` at line 1350): gets client, builds `RenameRequest{args[0], args[1]}`, calls `client.Rename()`, prints `renamed 'X' to 'Y'`\n- `renameCmd` cobra command (after `copyCmd`): `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `cobra.ExactArgs(2)`, `checkServerHeartbeat`\n- Register in both the env-docs `for` loop and `rootCmd.AddCommand()`",
